.TH BW-EDIT 1 "January 2026" "Bitwarden CLI" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bw-edit \- edit an object in the vault

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bw edit
\fIobject\fP \fIid\fP [\fIencodedJson\fP] [\fIoptions\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit an existing object in the vault. The object data should be provided as
base64-encoded JSON containing the complete updated object.

The recommended workflow is to get the existing object with \fBbw get\fP,
modify it, encode with \fBbw encode\fP, and then edit.

.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I object
Type of object to edit. Valid values:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B item
\- A vault item
.IP \(bu 2
.B item-collections
\- Update which collections an item belongs to
.IP \(bu 2
.B folder
\- A folder
.IP \(bu 2
.B org-collection
\- An organization collection
.RE
.TP
.I id
Object UUID to edit.
.TP
.I encodedJson
Base64-encoded JSON with updated object data. Can also be piped via stdin.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-organizationid\  id
Organization ID (required for item-collections and org-collection).

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Edit an item (update password):
.nf
$ bw get item 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 | jq '.login.password="newpassword"' | bw encode | bw edit item 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
.fi
.TP
Rename a folder:
.nf
$ bw get folder 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 | jq '.name="New Name"' | bw encode | bw edit folder 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
.fi
.TP
Update item collections (assign to collections):
.nf
$ echo '["collection-id-1","collection-id-2"]' | bw encode | bw edit item-collections 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 --organizationid org-id
.fi
.TP
Add a URI to a login item:
.nf
$ bw get item 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 | jq '.login.uris += [{"uri":"https://example.com"}]' | bw encode | bw edit item 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
.fi
.TP
Add a custom field to an item:
.nf
$ bw get item 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 | jq '.fields += [{"name":"API Key","value":"secret","type":1}]' | bw encode | bw edit item 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
.fi

.SH NOTES
.TP
\(bu
Requires an active session (vault must be unlocked).
.TP
\(bu
The encoded JSON must contain the complete object, not just the changed fields.
.TP
\(bu
All JSON must be base64-encoded. Use \fBbw encode\fP for this.
.TP
\(bu
Changes are synced to the server immediately.
.TP
\(bu
To edit collections for an organization item, use \fBitem-collections\fP.

.SH FIELD TYPES
When adding custom fields, the \fBtype\fP values are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B 0
\- Text
.IP \(bu 2
.B 1
\- Hidden
.IP \(bu 2
.B 2
\- Boolean
.IP \(bu 2
.B 3
\- Linked
.RE

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Object edited successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Edit failed or error occurred.

